suite.doc:
The UE reports all detected/strongest cells above a given threshold. Therefore, it may report strong cells whose PCI are currently not yet known to the eNB. In this case, the eNB looks up the C-plane IP connectivity information (IP address in the "PCI/RF/IP-address" look-up table) of the relevant neighbor eNB which is hosting the unknown cell. If the eNB successfully looks up the IP connectivity information and if there is not yet an X2 interface established to this neighbor site, the X2 signalling connectivity is set up. When network domain security is applied, dedicated, preconfigured IPsec tunnels are used for carrying the X2 signaling traffic between each individual eNB and the SEG. Within this procedure, the C-plane IP addresses of the adjacent eNBs are updated (learnt) in the MOCs "LNADJ" of both eNBs.
Analogous to the X2_C interfaces, the X2 UP interfaces (X2_U) are using preconfigured IPsec tunnels between each individual eNB and the SEG, if network domain security is applied. The U-plane addresses which are signaled by the Target eNB are used by the Source eNB for forwarding user data to the Target eNB. No address learning is required for the U-plane addresses.
